\title{Critical section}

\p{A region of code that accesses shared state in a way that is incorrect if more than one [[63U3]] executes it concurrently. Critical sections are exactly the regions that need protection by a synchronization primitive: a [[Q2DT]] excludes other threads while one is inside; a [[9QUX]] forces all threads to reach the same point before any may continue.}

\p{The art of writing correct concurrent code is to identify critical sections and protect them — without making them so large that you lose all parallelism.}
